This paper is about improving spoken language understanding (SLU) for building spoken dialog systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a novel deep neural network model for semantic frame parsing that incorporates user information to improve performance and reduce training time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and speech processing. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The paper proposes a new model architecture, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category. The paper uses the ATIS benchmark dataset, which is commonly used in NLP research, so cs.SD (Software Engineering) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and classification, so cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely but still possible category.
